  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>potato wedges</strong> to a baking tray, drizzle them with <strong>vegetable oil</strong>,<strong> </strong>then season<strong> </strong>with <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>smoked paprika </strong>(save the rest for later!) and a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 25 min until crisp – these are your <strong>paprika wedges</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676987864856-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676987864856-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676987864856-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676987864856-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676987864856-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potato wedges are cooking, trim, then finely chop the<strong> spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, separating the whites and greens</p><p>Combine the <strong>lean pork mince</strong> with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>smoked</strong> <strong>paprika</strong> and<strong> chopped spring onion whites</strong> in a bowl and season very generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Divide and shape into 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> patties and refrigerate until step 6 (this helps them hold their shape whilst cooking) – these are your <strong>paprika lean pork patties</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676987878683-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676987878683-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676987878683-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676987878683-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676987878683-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a high heat</p><p>Slice the <strong>brioche buns</strong> in half</p><p>Once the pan is hot, add the <strong>brioche halves</strong>, cut-side down, and cook for 3 min or until lightly toasted</p><p>Once toasted, set aside until serving and reserve the pan</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? You may need to do this in batches!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1676987896838-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1676987896838-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1676987896838-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1676987896838-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1676987896838-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel the <strong>red onions</strong>, then slice into thin rings</p><p>Return the reserved pan with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>to a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> red onion rings</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until the onions have started to caramelise</p><p>Once caramelised, set aside until serving and reserve the pan – these are your <strong>caramelised onion rings</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1676987907162-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1676987907162-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1676987907162-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1676987907162-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1676987907162-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine<strong> </strong>the<strong> red wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>remaining sliced spring onion</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>in a bowl – this is your<strong> salad dressing</strong></p><p>Thinly slice the <strong>apple<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (skin on), then add to the salad dressing and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>dressed apple</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1676987918379-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1676987918379-x400.jpg",
